{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐκλείπ-ω</b>, <br /> <b>leave out, pass over,</b> πολλὰ δ᾽ ἐκλείπω λέγων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 513; ἐ. ὄχλον λόγων [prev. author] “Pr.” 827, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.47 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. Ἄνδρον <b>leave out, pass over</b> Andros, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.33; ἐ. ὁτιοῦν τῆς παρασκευῆς 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.48; τὴν στρατιάν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 5.2.22; εἴ τι ἐξέλιπον, σὸν ἔργον ἀναπληρῶσαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 188e:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, ὄνειδος οὐκ ἐκλείπεται <b>fails</b> not <b>to appear,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 97. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>forsake, desert, abandon,</b> τὰς πατρίδας, τὴν ξυμμαχίην, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.169, 6.13, etc.; θήρας μόχθον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 52; τὸ ξυνώμοτον 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.74; τὸν ὅρκον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 750 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>abandon, quit,</b> τὴν τάξιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.24, +others; τὴν χώρην [prev. author] 4.105, 118, +others; τὸν πλοῦν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 911, compare 58 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>give up,</b> τὴν τυραννίδα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.123; τὰ ὑπάρχοντα 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.144; θρήνους 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1635; see below 11.2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> frequently in elliptic phrases, ἐκλείπειν τὴν πόλιν εἰς τὰ ἄκρα <b>abandon</b> the city <b>and go</b> to the heights, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.100, compare 8.50, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.4.2; ἐξέλειπον οἴκους πρὸς ἄλλον εὐνάτορα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 1040 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> εἴ τις ἐξέλιπε τὸν ἀριθμόν (of the Persian immortals) if any one <b>left</b> the number <b>incomplete,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.83. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>fail</b> one, ἐκλελοίπασιν ὑμᾶς αἱ προφάσεις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 8.16, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 657d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i>, of the Sun or Moon, <b>suffer eclipse,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.28; in full, ὁ ἥλιος ἐκλιπὼν τὴν ἐκ τοῦ οὐρανοῦ ἕδρην 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.37; ἐ. τὰς ὁδούς 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nu.” 584. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>die,</b> οἱ ἐκλιπόντες the <b>deceased,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 856e; τῶν ἄλλων ἐκλελοιπότων 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 11.10, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of trees, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “BGU” 1120.33 (1st c.BC)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; more frequently in full, ἐ. βίον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1131 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὑφ᾽ ὧν ἥκιστα ἐχρῆν τὸν βίον ἐκλιπών (=ἀποθανών) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 1.21; so ἐ. φάος 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1186, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>faint,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προρρητικόν” 1.71. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> generally, <b>leave off, cease,</b> τῇ μοι [ὁ λόγος] ἐξέλιπε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.239; ἐ. πυρετός 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 4.56, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.87 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐκλέλοιπεν εὐφρόνη, i.e. it is day, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 19; ὥστε μὴ 'κλιπεῖν κλέος [prev. work] 985, compare 1149 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [αἱ ἐργασίαι] ἐκλελοίπασιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, <b>leave off</b> doing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 234b, compare 249b: with _genitive_, θεραπείας 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Marcellus” 17. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>fail, be wanting,</b> ῥώμη γὰρ ἐκλέλοιπεν ἣν πρὶν εἴχομεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 230, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 485d; τῶν ἐπιτηδείων ἐκλειπόντων 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 16.75; ἡ φωνὴ ἐξέλιπε 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 35 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; περὶ ὧν ἐ. [ὁ νόμος] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1286a37 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: Grammars, of words in a sentence, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 11.17 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of grammatical forms,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 168.21. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <b>remain, be left,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.4Ki.7.13. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.7</b></Level3> <b>depart,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 128 (Lyric poetry), “Th.” 219. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.8</b></Level3> ἐκλείπων σφυγμός <b>remittent</b> pulse, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 9.66. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1587","accentedUnicode":"ἐκλείπω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0413","matchingForm":"ἀνέκλειπτος","stepTransliteration":"anekleiptos","gloss":"inexhaustible","_zh_tw_Gloss":"用不盡","_es_Gloss":"inagotable","_zh_Gloss":"用不尽"},{"strongNumber":"G1537","matchingForm":"ἐκ","stepTransliteration":"ek","gloss":"out from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de ","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G1590","matchingForm":"ἐκλύω","stepTransliteration":"ekluō","gloss":"to faint","_zh_tw_Gloss":"灰心, 就沮喪了","_es_Gloss":"desmayarse ","_zh_Gloss":"灰心, 就沮丧了"},{"strongNumber":"G3007","matchingForm":"λείπω","stepTransliteration":"leipō","gloss":"to lack","_zh_tw_Gloss":"缺少","_es_Gloss":"faltar","_zh_Gloss":"缺少"}],"shortDef":"to fail, end, stop","mediumDef":"to fail, end, stop <br /><b>to fail, die out,</b> <ref='Luk.22.32'>Lk. 22:32</ref>; <b>to come to an end,</b> <ref='Heb.1.12'>Heb. 1:12;</ref> <b>to be defunct,</b> <ref='Luk.16.9; 23:45'>Lk. 16:9; 23:45</ref>*","stepGloss":"to fail","stepTransliteration":"ekleipō","count":4,"_es_Definition":"faltar, faltar ; cesar, terminar ; dejar, dejar atrás (LUC.16:9)","_zh_tw_Definition":"失靈, 用盡, 消失 (路 16:9, 22:3; 來 1:12)","_zh_Definition":"失灵, 用尽, 消失 (路 16:9, 22:3; 来 1:12)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"giảm sút; yếu; chểnh mảng; chết dần. gồm: * Tiền tố  : ἐκ (G1537): ở ngoài, ra ngoài. * Động từ: λείπω (G3007): rời khỏi.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"窮盡, 錢財無用","_es_Gloss":"fallar ","_zh_Gloss":"穷尽, 钱财无用"}]}